Superfom Ltd team visited Ruiru Rehabilitation Centre in Ruiru Town on Tuesday 30 th October,
2018 where it donated baby mattresses as part of its Corporate Social Responsibility program. “This move is a strong indicator of our commitment to ensure that business is not only feasible
in the long term for our consumers but also for the communities around us,” said the marketing
manager Superfoam Ltd. Also speaking at the event, Anurag Shah, the sales manager cited that
it was important for businesses to ensure that communities living around them have a sense of
belonging and co-exist in a complimentary manner. The home’s administration appreciated the gesture of kindness and urged other like-minded well-wishers to emulate Superfoam Ltd and make a change in society.